<document>
  <properties>
    <title>How to install embargo plugin</title>
    <subtitle>Document on how to install the embargo plugin</subtitle>
  </properties>
  <body>
    <section name="How to install the embargo plugin">
      <subsection name="Prerequisites">
        <p>
          These instruction assumes that you have an HST project based on the HST archetype, i.e.
          a Maven multiproject consisting of at least three submodules: cms, site and content.
        </p>
      </subsection>
      <subsection name="Maven 2 repository">
        <p>Add this repository to your root pom.xml (if it has not already been defined in a parent pom):</p>
        <source><![CDATA[
<repository>
  <id>hippo-forge</id>
  <name>Hippo Forge maven 2 repository.</name>
  <url>http://maven.onehippo.com/maven2-forge/</url>
  <snapshots>
    <enabled>false</enabled>
  </snapshots>
  <releases>
    <updatePolicy>never</updatePolicy>
  </releases>
  <layout>default</layout>
</repository>]]></source>
      </subsection>

      <subsection name="Installation in CMS/Repository">
        <ol>
          <li>
            <p>Add these two dependency to the pom.xml of your <i>cms</i> module:</p>
            <source><![CDATA[
<dependency>
  <groupId>org.onehippo.forge.embargo</groupId>
  <artifactId>embargo-addon-frontend</artifactId>
  <version>...</version>
</dependency>]]></source>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p>Add these two dependency to the pom.xml of your <i>cms</i> module:</p>
            <source><![CDATA[
<dependency>
  <groupId>org.onehippo.forge.embargo</groupId>
  <artifactId>embargo-addon-repository</artifactId>
  <version>...</version>
</dependency>]]></source>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p>In case you're upgrading from version 1.01.05 it's advised to also include:</p>
            <source><![CDATA[
<dependency>
  <groupId>org.onehippo.forge.embargo</groupId>
  <artifactId>embargo-addon-repository-updaters</artifactId>
  <version>...</version>
</dependency>]]></source>

          </li>
          <li>
            <p>
              Rebuild your project. After startup, you should have the embargo workflow and an example embargo-enabled usergroup.
            </p>
          </li>
        </ol>
      </subsection>
    </section>
  </body>
</document>
